From e0c52309e8380b33239b16a85fbedb5da7d12675 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dale Whinham <daleyo@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 12 May 2025 18:37:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] wifi: ath12k: add devicetree disable-rfkill support

Some devices, including Microsoft Surface Pro 11, indicate through ACPI
feature flags that the ath12k rfkill path should be disabled. When Linux is
booted through devicetree instead of ACPI, that ACPI flag is unavailable and
the WCN7850 device can remain hard-blocked.

Carry the same intent through devicetree with a boolean disable-rfkill
property on the ath12k device node.

Based on dwhinham/kernel-surface-pro-11 commit e0c52309e8.
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
index 5d494c5cdc..954028495e 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/core.c
@@ -80,6 +80,10 @@ static int ath12k_core_rfkill_config(struct ath12k_base *ab)
 	if (ath12k_acpi_get_disable_rfkill(ab))
 		return 0;
 
+	if (ab->dev->of_node &&
+	    of_property_read_bool(ab->dev->of_node, "disable-rfkill"))
+		return 0;
+
 	for (i = 0; i < ab->num_radios; i++) {
 		ar = ab->pdevs[i].ar;
 
-- 
